A tragic plane crash near Polewali in West Sulawesi claimed the lives of at least 90 people, including three Americans from one family named Scott Jackson, Stephanie, and Lindsay.
The Adam Air Boeing 737-400 disappeared between Java and Sulawesi, prompting criticism for slow search and rescue efforts.
Indonesian President expressed concern over the recent disasters, blaming violent weather conditions.
The cause of the crash remains unknown, with rescue teams finding the wreckage in a mountainous region.
Chinese Foreign Minister extended condolences, while the Indonesian Navy prepared to transport the victims' bodies.
